.TH "amdgpu_bo_create" 9 "amdgpu_bo_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
amdgpu_bo_create \- create an &amdgpu_bo buffer object
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" amdgpu_bo_create
.BI "(struct amdgpu_device *adev "  ","
.BI "struct amdgpu_bo_param *bp "  ","
.BI "struct amdgpu_bo **bo_ptr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adev" 12
amdgpu device object
.IP "bp" 12
parameters to be used for the buffer object
.IP "bo_ptr" 12
pointer to the buffer object pointer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Creates an \fIamdgpu_bo\fP buffer object; and if requested, also creates a
shadow object.
Shadow object is used to backup the original buffer object, and is always
in GTT.
.SH "RETURN"
0 for success or a negative error code on failure.
